commit.message: v1.3.2.2-r2: allow containers-0.7
v1.3.2.2-r1: allow text-2.1
v1.3.2.2 Bump and CHANGELOG

New cabal flag `doctest` to control building the doctest test-suite

`doctest-parallel` typically is not available for GHC prereleases.
Now the doctest suite switches itself off automatically if it cannot build.

Refactor regexec (6 times) to not use partial functions tail and !0

This avoids triggering the x-partial warning of GHC 9.8.
CI: constraint-set bytestring-0.12
v1.3.2.1-r1: allow bytestring-0.12
Bump Haskell CI to latest GHCs: 9.6.2 9.2.8

Type the unsafeCoerce#

I noticed unsafeCoerce# in https://github.com/haskell-hvr/regex-tdfa/pull/52
and it look scary.

With this small change we see what the target type of coercion,
which makes it slightly less scary.

Especially as we use `unsafeCoerce` (without the hash),
so we don't (accidentally) coerce between difference runtime reps.
Fix return type in `memcpy` FFI signature

commit.message:
v1.3.2.1 bump and CHANGELOG

Had to resist the temptation to name this documentation patch release
`1.3.2.0`, :-D.
Fix #50: haddock rendering of code examples with escapes in strings
Bump CI to latest GHC minor versions 9.6.1, 9.4.5, 9.2.7
Bump CI to GHC 9.6.1 alpha2, 9.4.4 and 9.2.6
Bump to 1.3.2 and CHANGELOG
Extend and polish haddock for `Pattern` module
Fix #16: export `decode{PatternSet|CharacterClass}` from `Pattern`
Bump to 1.3.1.5 and CHANGELOG

Fix #1 (again) with proper test

Ranges beginning with `-` were not recognized.

Write GHC environment files so parallel-doctest picks up correct package.
Bump to 1.3.1.4 and CHANGELOG
CI: limit tests to GHC < 9.4 because of doctest-parallel
CI: limit tests to GHC >= 8.2 because of doctest-parallel
Doc test for #1
Add doc-test testsuite, fixing doc examples

Fix #1 by removing check on dash in regex parser

There are no illegal occurrences of `-` in a bracket expression.
Those that are separators of a range (e.g. `a-z`) are simply standing
for themselves.  A dash can even be an start or end point of a range,
as in `[--@]`.
ReadRegex: Raise correct error for empty char range (see #1)
ReadRedex: document BracketElement alternatives
Type signatures for parsers in ReadRedex
Fix #13 by linking documentation of `defaultCompOpt` (`regex-base`)

Fix #21 (deprecation warnings) by correct `MIN_VERSION_containers(0,5,11)`

Actually, correct would be `MIN_VERSION_containers(0,5,10,2)`, and the
warning is still raised for `containers-0.5.10.2`.  However, there is
no 4-ary version of this ternary macro.
